title: For Sale:  Modified 870 (Read Description)
postcontent: Hey, all. Selling an 870 that has been customized. Tube extension, new spring and follower and duracoated in coyote/flat dark earth. Fleur des lis carved stock and formed.  Also has rifle sights.That said, some of the duracoat got into the chamber. The gun fires fine but it causes some shells to stick and not seat all the way.  The duracoat was done by a gunsmith who declined to correct the issue and, frankly, I really never shoot the gun and it's been sitting in a case.  I'm selling it as a "gunsmith special" with probably minimal work or would be a fantastic gun to build on. I purchased it lightly used several years ago in the Wingmaster configuration and added the extended tube and a ghost ring rifle sight (which is not included with this shotgun).  The bluing on the original was not to my liking and I had it duracoated by a gunsmith - after which the feeding issue was noted.  Otherwise the gun is in fantastic condition.  There's also a spot on the receiver where a bit of overspray caused a blemish - I tried to get a photo but it's hardly noticeable and I couldn't get a clear shot of it.  I've installed the rare fleur des lis stock set that came with the gun.  I've fired the gun twice since refinishing and cleaned it.  I'll also include the original spring and follower should you want to remove the tube extension and clamp (both factory Remington parts).  If you want it blued or parkerised - I recently learned that Remington and Wilson combat provide those refinishing services and should have looked into it further in the first place. Ive priced it to sell quickly and hassle free.  I have quite a few shotguns and have had plenty of time to fix this one and haven't so I'm selling to accessorize a new carry pistol. Located in Wheeling near Oglebay - happy to meet somewhere closer to Wheeling itself.  Feel free to text me : REDACTED
